From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karel Tucek <kareltucek@centrum.cz>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 15:07:53 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Reboot after boot-mode serial recovery timeout

When the device is rebooted into the bootloader via the BOOT_MODE
retention flag (i.e. Agent's reenumerate command) and the serial
recovery window expires without any SMP traffic, MCUboot would
fall through to the post-recovery flow. Because USB CDC ACM was
already enumerated by the bootloader, the host stays attached to
the bootloader USB device and never sees the application
re-enumerate, making the keyboard appear stuck in the bootloader.

Force a cold reboot when boot_serial_enter() returns from the
boot-mode path. On the subsequent boot the BOOT_MODE flag is
already cleared, so MCUboot proceeds directly to chainload the
application with a fresh USB stack.
---
 boot/zephyr/main.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/boot/zephyr/main.c b/boot/zephyr/main.c
index 865fd7b6..790d00f1 100644
--- a/boot/zephyr/main.c
+++ b/boot/zephyr/main.c
@@ -28,6 +28,7 @@
 #include <zephyr/usb/usb_device.h>
 #include <soc.h>
 #include <zephyr/linker/linker-defs.h>
+#include <zephyr/sys/reboot.h>

 #if defined(CONFIG_BOOT_DISABLE_CACHES)
 #include <zephyr/cache.h>
@@ -884,6 +885,7 @@ int main(void)
          */
         BOOT_LOG_DBG("Staying in serial recovery");
         boot_serial_enter();
+        sys_reboot(SYS_REBOOT_COLD);
     }
 #endif

